Title: Ring with Cartouche-Shaped Bezel
Dimensions: Cartouche Bezel L: 2 5/16 x W: 2 7/16 x D: 1/2 in. (5.93 x 6.23 x 1.28 cm); Inner Diam.: 1/2 in. (1.23 cm)
Description: This example of turquoise-colored faience is chipped and has incrustations in the deeply cut, crisp hieroglyphs which read "May your house flourish, may your lifetime be jubilant under the gifts of Amun of Karnak (and) a high old age."
Provenance: Dikran Kelekian, New York and Paris, [date and mode of acquisition unknown] [obtained in Luxor]; Henry Walters, Baltimore, 1913, by purchase; Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.
Creator: Egyptian
